            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.School_Object__r.Id</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsNull</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>false</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.School_Object__r.Premium_Customer_Start_Date__c</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsNull</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>false</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>Update_Original_Close_Date_on_Account</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <label>Yes</label>
        </rules>
    </decisions>
    <description>This flow assigns SaaS Owner and Billing Upsell Owner roles to accounts linked with premium schools. Additionally, it fills in the Original Close Date for accounts where this field is null, based on specified criteria, and confirms that accounts associated with premium schools are correctly classified as &quot;Customer.&quot;
06/10 - PE - Updated entry criteria to remove looking at Number of Sites on the account and moved the criteria as a decision node to look at that field on the related school object.
06/12/24 - PE - Updated entry criteria
09/05/24 - PE - Added inactive prospects to the entrance criteria.
09/17/24 - PE - Removed SaaS Ofline Payer from entrance criteria
09/25/24 - PE - Added logic to exclude SaaS Ofline Payer when checking if an account has to be flipped back to customer
11/25/24 - PE - Added logic not to update accounts that have a cancelation request case where JG Cancelation Status is pending.
05/27/25 - PE - Added logic to skip updates to Customer Status if related case has a future date in the field Delayed Subscription Change Date</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <description>Date the field Brightwheel Plan was upgraded, minus one.</description>
        <name>forD_OriginalCloseDate</name>
        <dataType>Date</dataType>
        <expression>DATEVALUE({!currentItem_Filter_Changes_to_Premium.CreatedDate}) - 1</expression>
    </formulas>
